subSubSection.paragraph:
Paleoenvironment. The occurrences in the Vienna Basin represent shallow water settings with sea grass meadows (e.g. Gainfarn;
Zuschin et al . 2007
). This ecological preference is an additional argument for a separation from
C. exaltatus
, which is typically found in offshore clays.

